OL,3,GGrampian
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA frosty, dry and sunny start
OL,6,Fto the day will be followed by
OL,7,Fbuilding cloud during the morning and
OL,8,Fafternoon, perhaps the odd spot of
OL,9,Frain over Deeside towards evening.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FLargely dry at first but
OL,12,Fbecoming cloudy through the evening
OL,13,Fand overnight with some patchy light
OL,14,Frain for Deeside, staying dry in the
OL,15,Fnorth. Freshening southeast winds
OL,16,Faround the coast.
OL,17,
OL,18,CWednesday:FLargely cloudy as bands of
OL,19,Frain push northeast in the morning.
OL,20,FTurning showery later, these showers
OL,21,Fheavy and thundery at times.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
